    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA195-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu kaḷaviṉkaṇ neṭuṅkālam vantoḻuka vāṟṟāḷāyiṉa tōḻi varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante urged for marriage who was unable to bear it when during the secret phase a long time came [and] passed.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA195">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            aruḷā yākalō koṭitē yiruṅkaḻik</l>
<l>            kuruḷai nīrnāy koḻumīṉ māntit</l>
<l>            tillaiyam potumpiṟ paḷḷi koḷḷu</l>
<l>            mellam pulampa yāṉkaṇ ṭiciṉē</l>
<l>            kalleṉ puḷḷiṉ kāṉalan toṇṭi </l>
<l>            nellari toḻuvar kūrvā ḷuṟṟeṉap</l>
<l>            pallitaḻ tayaṅkiya kūmpā neyta</l>
<l>            ṉīralait tōṟṟam pōla</l>
<l>            vīriya kaluḻunī nayantōḷ kaṇṇē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>That you should not be considerate?</l>
<l rend="indent4">It [is] cruel,</l>
<l>o tender man from the lonely [seashore],</l>
<l rend="indent2">where the young otter feeds on rich fish in the dark backwaters</l>
<l rend="indent2">[and] takes a resting place in the grove of Tillai trees,</l>
<l rend="indent4">– I saw:</l>
<l>The eyes of her you longed for are dimming, wet</l>
<l rend="indent2">as the water-wrought appearance</l>
<l rend="indent2">of the blue waterlilies that don't close, [their] petals glittering<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">tayaṅkiya kūmpā</term>: we have to read this as two peyareccams in a row, which is quite rare.</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent">as they fall<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">uṟṟeṉa</term>: here we have a fairly clear instance where the abs. + <term xml:lang="ta">eṉa</term> is rather temporal than causal.</note> under the sharp blades of the paddy-cutting workmen,</l>
<l rend="indent3">in Toṇṭi with seashore groves noisy with birds.</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
